# Netlify / Cloudflare Pages routing.
#
# This is a two-entry Vite build: index.html is the marketing landing page,
# app.html is the application. Static files are matched before these rules, so
# real assets (/assets/*, /pwa-*.png) are unaffected.
#
# The order matters. A single catch-all to /index.html — what this file used to
# be — serves the LANDING page for /app and /settings, which silently breaks
# every auth flow: signup confirmation and password reset redirect to /app, and
# the GitHub OAuth callback returns to /settings.

/                 /index.html   200
/app              /app.html     200
/app/*            /app.html     200
/settings         /app.html     200
/settings/*       /app.html     200

# Anything else is an in-app route (the app rewrites its own URL), so hand it
# to the app rather than the landing page.
/*                /app.html     200
